{
  "doc_id": "12627",
  "text": "5 Histamine 2 receptor blockers (H 2 blockers), such as cimetidine and ranitidine have most often been used to prevent gastric lesions in both adults and infants treated in intensive care. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] The main eVect of H 2 blockers is to decrease the gastric acidity and to increase the gastric pH by inhibiting acid production. The serum concentration of ranitidine does not always correlate with gastric pH in neonates 10 11 and so this measurement cannot be used to determine the optimal ranitidine dose.",
